    "author_channel_id": "UChT9puGkwRd7CUiOb4h120g",
    "text": "Using voltage isn’t really useful, more accepted practice is constant current typically at 0.1 amps per square inch although you can run lower than that initially if you’re concerned about burning conductive paint. Also it’s generally better to limit your anode area to about twice the area of the piece(s)",
